<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="have-aux-v">have <strong><em>aux v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /həv/    美 /həv/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.****</h4>
<ul>
<li></li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He had taught here for 30 years by then.
那时他已经在这里教书30年了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I shall have done it by next week.
我将在下周之前做完。</p></div>

<ul>
<li></li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Had we followed his plan, we could have done the work better with less money and fewer people.
如果当初我们采纳了他的计划，就可以用更少的人力和财力把工作做得更好。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The dancer's incredible performance had the audience on its feet<strong><em>_</em></strong>__(clap) for 10 minutes at the end of the show.  （2020天津改）  </li>
<li>In art criticism, you must assume the artist has a secret message <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (hide) within the work.  （2015江苏改）  </li>
<li>It might have saved me some trouble <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (如果我知道) the schedule.  （2015 江苏改）  </li>
<li>Claire had her luggage <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (check) an hour before her plane left.  （2011 陕西改）  </li>
<li>Could you please tell me where you bought the shoes you had <strong><em>_</em></strong>_yesterday?  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. clapping  2. hidden  3. had I known / if I had known  4. checked  5. on  </p></div>